General James Jones, who was President Barack Obama's former national security advisor in 2009 and 2010, has commented on Iran's turbulent past week.

Speaking to CNBC's Hadley Gamble at the Atlantic Council in Abu Dhabi, he said “Qasem Soleimani’s death makes the region safer” and that “Trump was absolutely correct in taking out terrorist leader Soleimani".

